Botswana Says Signs Loans With World Bank, Open Fund for Transport Project

-- B y   J e r r y   B u n g u
-- 
2011-08-16T14:10:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/botswana-says-signs-loans-with-world-bank-open-fund-for-transport-project.html
Botswana signed loan agreements with
the  World Bank  and the OPEC Fund for International Development
to help pay for transport infrastructure, the ministry of
finance and development planning said.  The southern African nation will receive $186 million from
the World Bank and a $40 million loan from the OPEC Fund, known
as OFID, the Gaborone-based ministry said in an e-mailed
statement today.  The government will contribute the rest of money for the
$385 million project, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jerry Bungu in Gaborone at 
 jbungu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  